ense in Q1 2026.\n\n**3. Future Outlook & Financial Context:**\n*   The company expects a **multi-year investment horizon** before these AI infrastructure deployments translate into sustained positive Segment Adjusted EBITDA.\n*   **AI Segment Losses:** This massive capex is occurring alongside significant operating losses. In Q1 2026, the AI segment had a loss from operations of $(2,469) million and negative Segment Adjusted EBITDA of $(609) million.\n*   **Rationale:** The filing emphasizes that AI is a "nascent and rapidly evolving technology" where the commercial value proposition of frontier models remains largely unproven, justifying the high upfront investment risk.\n\n**4. Historical Growth Trajectory:**\n*   AI capex has grown exponentially: from **$463 million** in 2023 to **$5.6 billion** in 2024, **$12.7 billion** in 2025, and already **$7.7 billion** in just Q1 2026.\n\nIn summary, the filing documents a dramatic and accelerating capital expenditure program in the AI segment, overwhelmingly focused on building out terrestrial data center and compute infrastructure to support AI growth, despite the segment currently operating at a significant loss.',
